title: Add check for query limits
body:
Google limits free users to under 2,500 requests per day, this checks to see if the user went over their request and throws an error if google returns an error as mentioned in #2.

I haven't tested that this works normally yet because in order to test whether it catches errors I had to make more than 2,500 requests. If google returns anything called `error_message`, even if it worked, then this will break and display the contents of `error_message`.

title: Storing API Key as environmental variable
body:
I made a few small changes:
- Turned the Google Maps API key into a variable that is stored in the package environment. That means it only needs to be defined once and does not need to be (but still can be) passed to `gmapsdistance` every single time. It can be set using `set.api.key("your-key")` and retrieved using `get.api.key()`.
- I'm now returning the final output as a list instead of as a data.frame (that also means `Status` is not returned as a factor variable anymore)
- Re-formatted the code here and there
- Updated the `Readme`
